verse.lines:
{lang-eng}When morning gilds the skies,
My heart awaking cries,
May Jesus Christ be praised!
Alike at work and prayer, to Jesus I repair;
May Jesus Christ be praised!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}The night becomes as day,
When from the heart we say,
May Jesus Christ be praised!
The pow’rs of darkness fear
When this sweet chant they hear;
May Jesus Christ be praised!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Ye nations of mankind, in this your concord find;
May Jesus Christ be praised!
Let all the earth around ring
Joyous with the sound;
May Jesus Christ be praised!{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Be this, while life is mine, my canticle divine;
May Jesus Christ be praised!
Be this th’eternal song thro’ all the ages long;
May Jesus Christ be praised!{/lang-eng}
